umap-description =
    uMap is a self-hosted map editor based on OpenStreetMap tile layers.

    It allows anyone to create custom maps with markers, lines, polygons, and popups
    containing rich content (text, images, links). Maps can be shared publicly, embedded
    in websites, or kept private. Useful for visualizing location-based data without
    relying on Google Maps or other proprietary services.

umap-features =
    - Create maps with markers, lines, and polygons
    - Rich popups with text, images, and links
    - Multiple OpenStreetMap tile layer options
    - Public, private, and link-only sharing modes
    - Embed maps in external websites via iframe
    - Import/export GeoJSON, KML, CSV, and GPX
    - Collaboration and map ownership controls
    - No account required for viewing public maps
